Perfect! Now I have enough information to provide a comprehensive guide. Let me compile my findings:

## Compound Components Architecture in shadcn/ui

I've thoroughly explored the shadcn/ui component library and identified clear patterns for implementing compound components. Here's what I found:

### **File Structure & Locations**

The components are organized in:
- **Component files**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/` - houses all UI component implementations
- **Demo files**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/` - contains demo and example files
- **Registry config**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` - registers all components with metadata

### **1. Compound Component Architecture**

All compound components follow this pattern:

**File**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/tabs.tsx`
- Exports multiple sub-components as named exports
- Uses `"use client"` directive for client-side interactivity
- Wraps Radix UI primitives with styling and behavior

Example structure:
```tsx
"use client"
import * as React from "react"
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority"
import { Tabs as TabsPrimitive } from "radix-ui"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

// Root component
function Tabs({ className, orientation = "horizontal", ...props }: ...) {
  return <TabsPrimitive.Root data-slot="tabs" ... />
}

// Subcomponent with CVA variants
const tabsListVariants = cva(...) // Variant definitions
function TabsList({ className, variant = "default", ...props }: ...) { ... }

// Additional subcomponents
function TabsTrigger({ className, ...props }: ...) { ... }
function TabsContent({ className, ...props }: ...) { ... }

// Export all together
export { Tabs, TabsList, TabsTrigger, TabsContent, tabsListVariants }
```

### **2. Key Patterns Identified**

#### **A. Data Slot Pattern**
Every component adds a `data-slot` attribute for CSS targeting and clarity:
```tsx
<TabsPrimitive.Root data-slot="tabs" ... />
<TabsPrimitive.List data-slot="tabs-list" ... />
<TabsPrimitive.Trigger data-slot="tabs-trigger" ... />
```

#### **B. Orientation Support**
Implemented via attributes and Tailwind data selectors:

**Tabs component** (`/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/tabs.tsx`):
```tsx
function Tabs({
  className,
  orientation = "horizontal",
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<typeof TabsPrimitive.Root>) {
  return (
    <TabsPrimitive.Root
      data-orientation={orientation}
      orientation={orientation}
      className={cn(
        "group/tabs flex gap-2 data-[orientation=horizontal]:flex-col",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}
```

**Separator component** (`/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/separator.tsx`):
```tsx
function Separator({
  className,
  orientation = "horizontal",
  decorative = true,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<typeof SeparatorPrimitive.Root>) {
  return (
    <SeparatorPrimitive.Root
      data-orientation={orientation}
      className={cn(
        "shrink-0 bg-border 
         data-[orientation=horizontal]:h-px data-[orientation=horizontal]:w-full 
         data-[orientation=vertical]:h-full data-[orientation=vertical]:w-px",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}
```

**Button Group component** (`/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/button-group.tsx`):
```tsx
const buttonGroupVariants = cva(
  "flex w-fit items-stretch ...",
  {
    variants: {
      orientation: {
        horizontal: "[&>*:not(:first-child)]:rounded-l-none ...",
        vertical: "flex-col [&>*:not(:first-child)]:rounded-t-none ...",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: { orientation: "horizontal" },
  }
)

function ButtonGroup({
  className,
  orientation,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & VariantProps<typeof buttonGroupVariants>) {
  return (
    <div
      data-slot="button-group"
      data-orientation={orientation}
      className={cn(buttonGroupVariants({ orientation }), className)}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}
```

#### **C. CSS Classes & Variants (CVA)**
Uses **Class Variance Authority** for variant management:

**Button component** (`/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/button.tsx`):
```tsx
const buttonVariants = cva(
  "inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-md ...",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90",
        destructive: "bg-destructive text-white hover:bg-destructive/90 ...",
        outline: "border bg-background shadow-xs hover:bg-accent ...",
        secondary: "bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80",
        ghost: "hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground ...",
        link: "text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline",
      },
      size: {
        default: "h-9 px-4 py-2 has-[>svg]:px-3",
        xs: "h-6 gap-1 rounded-md px-2 text-xs ...",
        sm: "h-8 gap-1.5 rounded-md px-3 ...",
        lg: "h-10 rounded-md px-6 ...",
        icon: "size-9",
        // ... more sizes
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
)

function Button({
  className,
  variant = "default",
  size = "default",
  asChild = false,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"button"> &
  VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> & {
    asChild?: boolean
  }) {
  const Comp = asChild ? Slot.Root : "button"
  return (
    <Comp
      data-slot="button"
      data-variant={variant}
      data-size={size}
      className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}

export { Button, buttonVariants }
```

#### **D. The `cn()` Utility**
Combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` for intelligent class merging:

**File**: `/apps/v4/lib/utils.ts`
```tsx
import { clsx, type ClassValue } from "clsx"
import { twMerge } from "tailwind-merge"

export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {
  return twMerge(clsx(inputs))
}
```

This allows safe class overrides without conflicts.

#### **E. Radix UI Integration**
All compound components wrap Radix UI primitives:
- Tabs wraps `Tabs as TabsPrimitive`
- Accordion wraps `Accordion as AccordionPrimitive`
- Dialog wraps `Dialog as DialogPrimitive`
- Navigation Menu wraps `NavigationMenu as NavigationMenuPrimitive`

### **3. Compound Component Examples**

#### **A. Tabs Component**
**File**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/tabs.tsx`

Sub-components: `Tabs`, `TabsList`, `TabsTrigger`, `TabsContent`, `tabsListVariants`

**Demo**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/tabs-demo.tsx`
```tsx
export default function TabsDemo() {
  return (
    <Tabs defaultValue="account">
      <TabsList>
        <TabsTrigger value="account">Account</TabsTrigger>
        <TabsTrigger value="password">Password</TabsTrigger>
      </TabsList>
      <TabsContent value="account">
        {/* Content here */}
      </TabsContent>
      <TabsContent value="password">
        {/* Content here */}
      </TabsContent>
    </Tabs>
  )
}
```

#### **B. Accordion Component**
**File**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/accordion.tsx`

Sub-components: `Accordion`, `AccordionItem`, `AccordionTrigger`, `AccordionContent`

**Demo**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/accordion-demo.tsx`
```tsx
export default function AccordionDemo() {
  return (
    <Accordion type="single" collapsible className="w-full" defaultValue="item-1">
      <AccordionItem value="item-1">
        <AccordionTrigger>Product Information</AccordionTrigger>
        <AccordionContent className="flex flex-col gap-4">
          {/* Content */}
        </AccordionContent>
      </AccordionItem>
      {/* More items */}
    </Accordion>
  )
}
```

#### **C. Card Component (Semantic)**
**File**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/card.tsx`

Sub-components: `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, `CardDescription`, `CardAction`, `CardContent`, `CardFooter`

All are div-based without Radix dependency - pure layout components.

#### **D. Breadcrumb Component**
**File**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/breadcrumb.tsx`

Sub-components: `Breadcrumb`, `BreadcrumbList`, `BreadcrumbItem`, `BreadcrumbLink`, `BreadcrumbPage`, `BreadcrumbSeparator`, `BreadcrumbEllipsis`

Uses `asChild` pattern with Radix `Slot.Root` for flexible composition.

#### **E. Dialog Component (Complex)**
**File**: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/dialog.tsx`

Sub-components: `Dialog`, `DialogTrigger`, `DialogPortal`, `DialogOverlay`, `DialogContent`, `DialogHeader`, `DialogTitle`, `DialogDescription`, `DialogFooter`, `DialogClose`

