      },
    ],
  },
```

> **No changes needed** to `new-york-v4/registry.ts` or `bases/radix/registry.ts` — both already spread `...ui` and `...examples` from their respective `_registry.ts` files.

---

## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| `StepperItemContext` default | `null` | Distinguishes "inside item" vs "standalone" usage in `StepperContent` |
| `StepperContent` step resolution | `itemCtx?.step ?? stepProp` | Works inside items (no prop needed) AND standalone (explicit `step` prop) |
| No Radix primitive | Pure React | No Radix stepper primitive exists |
| Separator position | Inside `StepperItem` (last child) | Reads `isCompleted` from item context; placed after `StepperTrigger` in horizontal items, between trigger and content in vertical |
| Separator visibility outside item | Supported via `className` prop | User places separator between items and sets margin manually |
| `"use client"` | Yes, on both component files | `useState` + click handlers require client runtime |

---

## Verification

1. **TypeScript**: `cd apps/v4 && tsc --noEmit` — no new errors (components use only React built-ins and `cn`)
2. **Registry schema**: Each `_registry.ts` exports `Registry["items"]` — Zod validation runs automatically during `pnpm registry:build`
3. **Render test**: Mount `<Stepper defaultValue={2}><StepperItem step={1} className="flex-1">…</StepperItem><StepperSeparator /><StepperItem step={2} className="flex-1">…</StepperItem></Stepper>` — step 1 should have `data-completed`, step 2 should have `data-active` and `aria-current="step"`
4. **Context isolation**: `<StepperContent step={2}>` used outside any `StepperItem` but inside `<Stepper value={2}>` should render; step 1/3 should not
5. **Orientation switch**: Toggling `orientation="vertical"` should change `data-orientation` on root div and the separator from `h-px flex-1` to `w-px flex-1`
6. **No existing "stepper"**: Confirm `grep -r '"stepper"' apps/v4/registry` returns no existing entry before adding

